                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Mumbai, Jan. 20 (PTI): Bombay High Court will decide whether a woman who got a job on compassionate grounds after her husbands death would become ineligible after remarriage.           gita, the petitioner, had got a job with the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation after the death of her husband, a civic employee. But after she remarried, the corporation sacked her. The court has given the civic body two weeks to file a written reply.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The government has provided a quick blood-clotting agent to paramilitary troops in combat zones to reduce loss of lives from excessive bleeding. The agent, Quik Clot, has been supplied by the Union home ministry to all operational areas.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The continued attacks on Indians in Australia do not augur well for bilateral ties, external affairs minister S.M. Krishna said on Wednesday. He was referring to the latest attack on an Indian taxi driver in Melbourne  the fifth in a week in Australia.                   
	Pune (PTI): About 120 students of the Symbiosis Institute of Management in Pune were hospitalised on Wednesday with symptoms of food poisoning. They fell ill after eating at the hostel mess on Tuesday night. The food samples have been sent for chemical analysis.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): A fire broke out at a closed textile mill at Dadar in central Mumbai on Wednesday. Some 22 fire engines and 10 water tankers took five hours to douse the fire. No injuries were reported. Officials suspect foul play. One of the mills was to be revived by the National Textile Corporation.                  Indore (PTI): A convict awarded life imprisonment for murder, escaped from the court even as the judge was writing the sentence on Tuesday, police said.
                                                                                                                                              
